  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Main of the study is to assess the influence of high-dose opioids on the sleep architecture
      and patterns of breathing using non-invasive polysomnographic measurements before and after
      opioid withdrawal in patient who undergo opioid withdrawal independently from the present
      study. These data will be compared to polysomnographic data of patients under opioid
      treatment who do not undergo opioid withdrawal as well as to patients without opioid
      treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
